text: I promised my therapist two weeksI opened up deeper than I ever have before to my therapist today  I admitted  twice this week I had almost ended it all  She asked me why  I replied that I needed control  Self harm had been my control but I had to chose between cutting and my boyfriend  Let s just say we are celebrating six months next week  Now the only control I feel is choosing to live or die  It is the fundamental choice that is mine alone  My therapist asked me  Can you stay safe these next two weeks  I said maybe  She replied   I want to see you at our next appointment  I look forward to hearing how things are with your job and boyfriend  I look forward to it  So can you promise me you will be here to tell me about it  I said yes  She asked me to say the promise out loud  I said  I promise to stay alive  then I broke down crying  She started crying as well  For the first time giving up that control felt like a release  I never thought promising someone to stay alive would bring me to such a state of tears and vulnerability  My therapist has helped me become so much more open  She has helped keep me alive  For that I am thankful
